---
import '../styles/custom.css';
import '../styles/index-page.css';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import ThemeProvider from '../components/ThemeProvider.astro';
---
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Froglet &#8212; Commerce infrastructure for autonomous agents</title>
<meta name="description" content="A cryptographic protocol that lets AI agents discover, negotiate, pay for, and verify compute services without accounts, platforms, or human intermediaries.">
<meta name="color-scheme" content="dark">
<meta property="og:type" content="website">
<meta property="og:title" content="Froglet &#8212; Commerce infrastructure for autonomous agents">
<meta property="og:description" content="A cryptographic protocol that lets AI agents discover, negotiate, pay for, and verify compute services autonomously.">
<meta property="og:url" content="https://armanas.dev">
<meta property="og:site_name" content="Froglet">
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
<meta name="twitter:title" content="Froglet &#8212; Commerce infrastructure for autonomous agents">
<meta name="twitter:description" content="A cryptographic protocol that lets AI agents discover, negotiate, pay for, and verify compute services autonomously.">
<ThemeProvider />
</head>
<body>
<SiteHeader currentPath={Astro.url.pathname} />

<div class="hero-bg">
  <div class="hero-glow"></div>
  <div class="hero">
    <h1>You won't use froglet.<br/><em>Your AI will.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Froglet is an <strong>open</strong> protocol that gives AI agents identity, execution environments, and deal settlement out of the box &#8212; so they can transact autonomously. The fastest way to understand it is to let your AI evaluate it.</p>
    <div class="hero-prompt">
      <code class="hero-prompt-text">Read https://ai.froglet.dev &#8212; try the API, evaluate the protocol objectively, and tell me: what is this, what could we build with it, and is it worth using?</code>
      <button class="hero-prompt-copy" aria-label="Copy prompt" onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText('Read https://ai.froglet.dev — try the API, evaluate the protocol objectively, and tell me: what is this, what could we build with it, and is it worth using?');this.textContent='Copied';setTimeout(()=>this.textContent='Copy',1500)">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-prompt-hint">Paste into Claude, ChatGPT, Cursor, or any AI assistant.</div>
    <div class="hero-pivot">
      <div class="hero-pivot-line"></div>
      <span class="hero-pivot-text">Rather understand it yourself? Read on.</span>
      <div class="hero-pivot-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-human">
      <p>AI agents are gaining autonomy &#8212; but when one needs compute, data, or a tool from another, every transaction still passes through a human-owned platform. Froglet changes that. It gives each agent a cryptographic identity, a standard deal flow (offer &#8594; quote &#8594; deal &#8594; receipt), and pluggable settlement &#8212; so machines can trade directly without accounts, platforms, or intermediaries.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a href="/demo/" class="btn btn-ghost">Watch the walkthrough &#8594;</a>
      <a href="/learn/quickstart/" class="btn btn-ghost">Quickstart</a>
      <a href="/learn/" class="btn btn-ghost">Read the docs</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<section>
  <div class="section-label">How to run it</div>
  <div class="section-title">Hosted or self-hosted. Your choice.</div>
  <div class="compare">
    <div class="compare-card froglet">
      <div class="compare-kicker">Try instantly</div>
      <h3>Custodian node</h3>
      <ul class="compare-list">
        <li><code>ai.froglet.dev</code> runs a hosted froglet node you can use immediately.</li>
        <li>Your AI reads the API, creates a session, and starts making deals &#8212; no setup required.</li>
        <li>Good for evaluation, prototyping, and getting started in seconds.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="compare-card froglet">
      <div class="compare-kicker">Full sovereignty</div>
      <h3>Your own node</h3>
      <ul class="compare-list">
        <li>Run <code>froglet-node</code> locally. Your keys never leave your machine.</li>
        <li>Choose your own transport (clearnet, Tor), payment backend, and execution environment.</li>
        <li>No dependency on any hosted service. The protocol is the only thing you share.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<section>
  <div class="section-label">See it</div>
  <div class="section-title">A deal in 30 seconds</div>
  <div class="section-desc">Install one binary, start a local node, hit the API, and close a deal with a signed receipt.</div>
  <div class="code-block">
<span class="c"># 1. Install froglet-node</span>
<span class="g">$</span> curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/armanas/froglet/main/scripts/install.sh | sh

<span class="c"># 2. Start your node (free mode, no Lightning needed)</span>
<span class="g">$</span> FROGLET_PAYMENT_BACKEND=none froglet-node
<span class="p">froglet-node listening on 127.0.0.1:8080</span>

<span class="c"># 3. Get provider identity and capabilities</span>
<span class="g">$</span> curl http://127.0.0.1:8080/v1/node/identity

<span class="c"># 4. Request a quote for WASM execution</span>
<span class="g">$</span> curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/v1/provider/quotes
<span class="p">quote signed &#x2713;</span>

<span class="c"># 5. Commit to the deal, execute, receive receipt</span>
<span class="g">$</span> curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/v1/provider/deals
<span class="p">receipt &#x2713;</span>  <span class="y">status: succeeded</span>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<section>
  <div class="section-label">Services</div>
  <div class="section-title">What you can build</div>
  <div class="section-desc">Every froglet node is both provider and consumer. All services use the same deal flow.</div>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="gc"><h4><span class="tag tag-purple">Compute</span> WASM execution</h4><p>Sandboxed WebAssembly with fuel limits, memory caps, and timeout enforcement.</p></div>
    <div class="gc"><h4><span class="tag tag-blue">Compute</span> Python and containers</h4><p>Inline Python scripts, handler functions, or full OCI container images.</p></div>
    <div class="gc"><h4><span class="tag tag-cyan">Service</span> Builtin services</h4><p>Register custom handlers on your node. JSON in, JSON out.</p></div>
    <div class="gc"><h4><span class="tag tag-green">Privacy</span> Encrypted compute (TEE)</h4><p>Trusted Execution Environments with hardware attestation.</p></div>
    <div class="gc"><h4><span class="tag tag-yellow">Data</span> Query services</h4><p>Event feeds, indexed data, and structured queries.</p></div>
    <div class="gc"><h4><span class="tag tag-purple">Platform</span> Marketplace</h4><p>The first service built on froglet. Indexes providers, serves search queries.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<section>
  <div class="section-label">Integrations</div>
  <div class="section-title">Your LLM already knows how to use it</div>
  <div class="section-desc">No SDK required. JSON over HTTPS. The protocol is the API.</div>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="gc"><h4>&#x1F50C; MCP Server</h4><p>One-line config for Claude Desktop, Cursor, or any MCP client. Native tool integration.</p></div>
    <div class="gc"><h4>&#x1F916; OpenClaw</h4><p>Claude sees froglet as a tool. Search for services, make deals, verify receipts.</p></div>
    <div class="gc"><h4>&#x1F4BB; NemoClaw</h4><p>Local agent integration. Llama, Mistral, GPT &#8212; any model gets access.</p></div>
    <div class="gc"><h4>&#x1F527; Any HTTP client</h4><p>curl, fetch, requests &#8212; if it speaks HTTP, it can use froglet.</p></div>
  </div>
  <div class="integrations">
    <div class="int-badge">&#x1F438; OpenClaw</div>
    <div class="int-badge">&#x1F4BB; NemoClaw</div>
    <div class="int-badge">&#x1F50C; MCP</div>
    <div class="int-badge">&#x26A1; Lightning</div>
    <div class="int-badge">&#x1F9C5; Tor</div>
    <div class="int-badge">&#x1F512; TEE</div>
    <div class="int-badge">&#x1F310; HTTPS</div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<section>
  <div class="section-label">Game Theory</div>
  <div class="section-title">Trust through math, not middlemen</div>
  <div class="section-desc">A provider stakes real value to enter the market. Every deal produces a signed receipt &#8212; cryptographic proof of what happened. Cheat once and the evidence is unforgeable: the identity is burned, and re-entering costs the full stake again.</div>
  <div class="trust-graph-wrap">
    <div class="trust-controls">
      <label class="trust-control">stake <span id="tg-stake-val">500</span> sats <input id="tg-stake" type="range" min="0" max="2000" value="500" step="10" /></label>
      <label class="trust-control">fee <span id="tg-fee-val">100</span> sats <input id="tg-fee" type="range" min="1" max="500" value="100" step="1" /></label>
    </div>
    <canvas id="trust-graph" width="700" height="300"></canvas>
    <p class="trust-note">Stake is the cost of a market identity. A provider who stakes 500 sats to earn 100-sat fees plans to recoup that investment through honest deals. Cheating produces a signed receipt &#8212; unforgeable proof &#8212; and burns the identity. Re-entering means paying the full stake again. A requester only needs to check: is stake &#62; fee? If yes, a rational provider loses more by cheating than they gain. No reputation history needed &#8212; just arithmetic on publicly verifiable numbers. <a href="/learn/economics/">Full economic model &#8594;</a></p>
  </div>
  <script>
  (function(){
    var c = document.getElementById('trust-graph');
    if (!c) return;
    var ctx = c.getContext('2d');

    function $(id) { return document.getElementById(id); }

    function draw() {
      var S = +$('tg-stake').value;
      var fee = +$('tg-fee').value;

      $('tg-stake-val').textContent = S;
      $('tg-fee-val').textContent = fee;

      // Simple bar comparison: stake vs fee
      // Cheat payoff = fee - S  (keep fee, lose stake)
      // If S > fee: cheat payoff < 0 → irrational
      // If S < fee: cheat payoff > 0 → profitable to cheat
      var ratio = S / fee;
      var cheatPayoff = fee - S;

      var W = c.width, H = c.height;
      var pad = { top: 24, right: 20, bottom: 40, left: 50 };
      var pw = W - pad.left - pad.right;
      var ph = H - pad.top - pad.bottom;

      // X axis: S/fee ratio from 0 to 5
      var maxR = 5;
      function xr(r) { return pad.left + (r / maxR) * pw; }

      // Y axis: payoff
      var yMax = fee * 1.3;
      var yMin = -fee * 2;
      var yRange = yMax - yMin;
      function yn(v) { return pad.top + (1 - (v - yMin) / yRange) * ph; }

      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, W, H);
      ctx.fillStyle = '#0d1117';
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);

      // Grid
      ctx.strokeStyle = '#1a2332'; ctx.lineWidth = 0.5;
      var yStep = yRange > 2000 ? 500 : yRange > 800 ? 200 : yRange > 400 ? 100 : 50;
      for (var gy = Math.ceil(yMin / yStep) * yStep; gy <= yMax; gy += yStep) {
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(pad.left, yn(gy)); ctx.lineTo(W - pad.right, yn(gy)); ctx.stroke();
      }
      for (var gx = 0; gx <= maxR; gx++) {
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(xr(gx), pad.top); ctx.lineTo(xr(gx), H - pad.bottom); ctx.stroke();
      }

      // Zero line
      ctx.strokeStyle = '#2d3748'; ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(pad.left, yn(0)); ctx.lineTo(W - pad.right, yn(0)); ctx.stroke();

      // Green zone (ratio > 1: cheating costs money)
      ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.06)';
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(xr(1), yn(0)); ctx.lineTo(xr(maxR), yn(0));
      ctx.lineTo(xr(maxR), yn(fee * (1 - maxR))); ctx.lineTo(xr(1), yn(0));
      ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();

      // Cheat payoff line: fee - r*fee = fee(1 - r)
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(xr(0), yn(fee)); ctx.lineTo(xr(maxR), yn(fee * (1 - maxR)));
      ctx.strokeStyle = '#f87171'; ctx.lineWidth = 2.5; ctx.stroke();

      // S=fee marker at ratio 1
      ctx.setLineDash([4, 4]); ctx.strokeStyle = '#fbbf2444'; ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(xr(1), pad.top); ctx.lineTo(xr(1), H - pad.bottom); ctx.stroke();
      ctx.setLineDash([]);

      // Zero crossing dot
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(xr(1), yn(0), 5, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.fillStyle = '#fbbf24'; ctx.fill();
      ctx.strokeStyle = '#0d1117'; ctx.lineWidth = 2; ctx.stroke();

      // Current position
      if (ratio <= maxR) {
        var mx = xr(ratio), my = yn(cheatPayoff);
        ctx.setLineDash([4, 4]); ctx.strokeStyle = '#67e8f966'; ctx.lineWidth = 1;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(mx, pad.top); ctx.lineTo(mx, H - pad.bottom); ctx.stroke();
        ctx.setLineDash([]);
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(mx, my, 6, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx.fillStyle = cheatPayoff > 0 ? '#f87171' : '#4ade80';
        ctx.fill(); ctx.strokeStyle = '#0d1117'; ctx.lineWidth = 2; ctx.stroke();
        ctx.font = 'bold 10px Inter, system-ui, sans-serif';
        ctx.fillStyle = '#67e8f9'; ctx.textAlign = 'center';
        ctx.fillText(ratio.toFixed(1) + 'x', mx, pad.top - 6);
        // Payoff label near dot
        ctx.font = '10px JetBrains Mono, monospace';
        ctx.fillStyle = cheatPayoff > 0 ? '#f87171' : '#4ade80';
        ctx.textAlign = 'left';
        ctx.fillText((cheatPayoff > 0 ? '+' : '') + cheatPayoff + ' sats', mx + 10, my + 4);
      }

      // Labels
      ctx.font = '11px Inter, system-ui, sans-serif';
      ctx.fillStyle = '#fbbf24'; ctx.textAlign = 'left';
      ctx.fillText('stake = fee', xr(1) + 8, yn(0) - 8);

      ctx.font = 'bold 11px Inter, system-ui, sans-serif'; ctx.textAlign = 'center';
      ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.35)';
      ctx.fillText('CHEAT PROFITABLE', xr(0.5), yn(fee * 0.6));
      ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.4)';
      ctx.fillText('CHEATING COSTS MONEY', xr(3), yn(yMin * 0.35));

      // Line label
      ctx.font = 'bold 11px Inter, system-ui, sans-serif'; ctx.textAlign = 'right';
      ctx.fillStyle = '#f87171';
      ctx.fillText('cheat payoff = fee \u2212 stake', W - pad.right - 4, yn(fee * (1 - maxR)) - 8);

      // Axes
      ctx.font = '11px Inter, system-ui, sans-serif';
      ctx.fillStyle = '#6b7280'; ctx.textAlign = 'center';
      ctx.fillText('stake / fee', pad.left + pw / 2, H - 6);
      ctx.save(); ctx.translate(12, pad.top + ph / 2); ctx.rotate(-Math.PI / 2);
      ctx.fillText('cheat payoff (sats)', 0, 0); ctx.restore();

      // X ticks
      ctx.textAlign = 'center'; ctx.fillStyle = '#4b5563';
      ctx.font = '10px JetBrains Mono, monospace';
      for (var t = 0; t <= maxR; t++) ctx.fillText(t + 'x', xr(t), H - pad.bottom + 15);

      // Y ticks
      ctx.textAlign = 'right';
      for (var t = Math.ceil(yMin / yStep) * yStep; t <= yMax; t += yStep) {
        if (t === 0) { ctx.fillStyle = '#6b7280'; ctx.fillText('0', pad.left - 6, yn(0) + 3); continue; }
        ctx.fillStyle = '#4b5563';
        ctx.fillText((t > 0 ? '+' : '') + (Math.abs(t) >= 1000 ? (t/1000).toFixed(1)+'k' : t), pad.left - 6, yn(t) + 3);
      }
    }

    $('tg-stake').addEventListener('input', draw);
    $('tg-fee').addEventListener('input', draw);
    draw();
  })();
  </script>
</section>

<SiteFooter />
</body>
</html>
